<p>Speaking of which, I checked the bliblical quote, and found this in the next verse but one: "If the clouds be full of rain, they empty themselves upon the earth: and if the tree fall toward the south, or toward the north, in the place where the tree falleth, there it shall be." Which is pretty deep, right?&#160;<a href="#fnref1:2" rev="footnote" class="footnote-backref">&#8617;</a></p>
